title: Matthew Perry autopsy results are inconclusive, pending toxicology report, authorities say
description: Matthew Perry's initial autopsy results are inconclusive pending a toxicology report, authorities said Sunday.

title: 13-year-old who allegedly stabbed mother to death in front of new baby to be charged as an adult
description: A 13-year-old Florida boy accused of fatally stabbing his mother as she was sleeping has been charged as an adult with first-degree murder.

title: Matthew Perry, beloved 'Friends' actor, remembered in photos
description: In Photos: the life of "Friends" actor Matthew Perry

title: Maine shootings leave deaf community reeling after 4 of their own are killed
description: Central Maine's tight-knit deaf community was hit particularly hard by this week’s mass shootings. A deaf cornhole tournament was attacked in the shootings.

title: LA is beefing with NYC again — over scooped bagels
description: One Angeleno’s hunt for a scooped bagel in New York City has the internet up in arms, reigniting the city’s long-running culture clash with Los Angeles.

title: Former NHL star Adam Johnson, 29, dies in 'freak accident' during U.K. hockey game
description: American hockey star Adam Johnson has died following a "freak accident" during a game for a British hockey league on Saturday.

title: Halloween weekend shootings leave at least 3 dead, over 40 injured
description: At least 3 people are dead and over 40 have been injured after multiple mass shootings across the country during the Halloween weekend, according to officials.

title: Full Panel: How long will Speaker Johnson’s ‘grace period’ last?
description: Stephen Hayes, Kelly O’Donnell, Toluse Olorunnipa, and Jen Psaki discuss Rep. Dean Phillips' (D-Minn.) recent bid for the 2024 presidency challenging President Biden, and look at Speaker Mike Johnson's (R-La.) tenure as a congressman.

title: Effects of psychedelics like magic mushrooms can last for days or weeks, new research finds
description: Learn more about the potential downsides of taking psychedelics such as "magic mushrooms" if you have mental health issues.

title: Manchin ‘stands out’ as a potential 2024 candidate, Schwarzenegger says
description: During an interview with Meet the Press, former Gov. Arnold Schwarzenegger (R-Calif.) tells Kristen Welker it’s all “Trump, Trump, Biden, Biden” in 2024, but potential candidates who could bring necessary leadership aren’t given enough space.

title: Jayapal on 2024: 'I am certainly concerned about [Biden's] approach' to Israel
description: Rep. Pramila Jayapal (D-Wash.) joins Meet the Press exclusively and says that, while she has been "one of President Biden's biggest supporters,” she worries that the president’s response to Israel will cost him support from Arab and Muslim voters.

title: Rock on: 'Devil comet' will bring its horns swooping by Earth this summer
description: A comet with two distinct “horns” of gas and ice, earning it the nickname “devil comet” is speeding through the inner solar system and may be visible to the naked eye in the spring when it reaches its closest point to Earth.

title: Florida is booming and burning more trash. Residents say it’s making them sick.
description: Officials want to expand waste-to-energy incinerators across Florida, which they say can be preferable to landfills. Critics worry the plants pose health risks.

title: Supreme Court wades into social media wars over free speech
description: Three major issues on the role of social media in society are before the Supreme Court, with oral arguments in the first two cases taking place this week.

title: Matthew Perry remembered: Friends, colleagues and fans react to death of beloved actor
description: News of the death of actor Matthew Perry on Saturday night triggered an immediate outpouring of shock and grief.

title: Matthew Perry, ‘Friends’ actor, dies of apparent drowning at 54
description: Matthew Perry died Saturday of an apparent drowning at his Pacific Palisades home, a representative for the actor and a law enforcement source say.

title: Auto workers union announces tentative agreement to end strike with Stellantis
description: The United Auto Workers union and Stellantis say they've reached a tentative agreement on a new contract, leaving General Motors as the only one of the Big Three automakers without a contract with the union.
